    "long_instructions": "### What Is Ransomware?\r\n\r\n**Ransomware** is a type of malware that locks or encrypts files on a computer, then demands payment (often in money or cryptocurrency) to restore access.\r\n\r\nIt is designed to create fear and urgency. Some ransomware uses countdown timers, threatening language, or personal details to pressure users into acting quickly before they think clearly.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Scenario\r\n\r\nYou are using your school laptop during a break and exploring a few files and folders on the desktop. Your job is to explore the desktop and see what happens when curiosity overrides caution.\r\n\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n**Step 1: Look Around**\r\n\r\nExplore the apps, files and folders on the desktop. See what looks normal and what catches your attention.\r\n\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n**Step 2: Run the Ransomware**\r\n\r\nEventually, you'll come across a file that, when opened, launches the ransomware.\r\n\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n",
